Bring a large #pot{} of water to a rapid boil with a pinch of @salt{}. Wash the @Brown Basmati Rice{300%g} under running water for ~{30%seconds} (important step!). Add your rice to the pot and cook for ~{10%minutes} on the heat, then remove from the heat with the lid on for ~{10%minutes}.

Cut the @Red Onion{1} in half through the root, peel and thinly slice into half moon shapes. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{3} (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one). Finely chop the @Red Chilli{1} and roughly chop the @Coriander{1}. Thinly slice the @Celery Stick{1} widthways. Remove the core from the @Yellow Pepper{1} and chop into 3cm chunks. Peel the @Ginger{2} using the edge of a #spoon{} and grate.

Cut the @Pork Medallion{4} into 2cm chunks, then dab it dry with #kitchen paper{}. Toss your pork in the @Cornflour{2.5%tbsp} together with a pinch of @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a #non-stick frying pan{} on high heat. Once really hot, carefully add your pork (it might sputter a bit). Stir-fry your pork for ~{3%minutes}. Remove your pork from the pan and cover in #tinfoil{} to keep warm.

> The pork is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Heat a splash of @oil{} to the now empty pan and add your onion, garlic, chilli and ginger. After ~{1%minute}, add your pepper and cook for ~{2%minutes} more. Add the @Sugar Snap Peas{1} and your celery and cook for ~{1%minute}. Add a splash of @water{}, cover the pan and cook for another ~{2%minutes}.

Squeeze a good splash of @Lime{1} juice into the @Hoisin Sauce{5%tbsp}. Take the lid off your veggies and add your hoisin sauce together with your pork. Toss everything together for ~{1%minute} and then serve your stir-fry with your brown rice on the side and your coriander sprinkled over.